' @id(USE-RUN-CYCLE)
' @id(USE-BROWSE-TREE)
' @id(USE-GROUP-BY-CYCLE)
' @id(USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW)
' @id(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
' @id(USE-ELEMENT-DESC)
' @id(USE-WHOLE-MAP)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
'
' Current-side use cases for cycle tracking, derived from the
' implemented code: the /mdd-cycle skill (templates::MDD_CYCLE_SKILL +
' .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-cycle/SKILL.md) and the mdd-viewer rail,
' Diff tab, and MODEL CONTEXT description block.
'
' @desc(USE-RUN-CYCLE, "Implemented as the /mdd-cycle skill: one-shot orchestration of the whole MDD loop from a single description, pausing for clarification.")
' @desc(USE-BROWSE-TREE, "Implemented: left rail is a VSCode-style collapsible directory tree (tree.rs TreeNode) instead of a flat list.")
' @desc(USE-GROUP-BY-CYCLE, "Implemented: rail Directory/By-cycle toggle groups diagrams under the cycle that touched them, read from .mdd/cycles/.")
' @desc(USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW, "Implemented: MddViewer::diff_ui keys on the rail-selected file; the CYCLE row lists only cycles whose CycleDiff for the file is !is_empty() (real added/removed change, a written .diff) via Project::cycles_with_diff_for — present-unchanged cycles excluded; default latest, caption when one, placeholder when none.")
' @desc(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM, "Implemented: diff_ui inner Diagram/List toggle — Diagram paints the file's rendered .diff.svg on the shared canvas (paint_canvas), List shows that file's added/removed/unchanged buckets.")
' @desc(USE-ELEMENT-DESC, "Implemented: selecting an @id shows its @desc text in a distinct DESCRIPTION block in the MODEL CONTEXT card.")
' @desc(USE-WHOLE-MAP, "Implemented: /mdd-cycle's Close step accumulates each cycle's diff into the persisted per-concept .mdd/map/ tree (added @ids copied in with ' @cycle provenance, removed dropped so add-then-remove nets to neither), refreshes .mdd/map/manifest.yml, and snapshots the tree to .mdd/cycles/<N>/whole/. An inspection artifact outside the parity gate.")
title MDD cycle tracking — use cases (current)

left to right direction

actor "Developer" as Dev <<added>>

rectangle "mdd toolchain + viewer" {
  usecase "Run a full MDD cycle\nfrom one description" as RunCycle
  usecase "Browse models in a\ndirectory tree (VSCode-style)" as Tree
  usecase "Group diagrams by cycle" as Group
  usecase "View the selected file's\nbefore/after diff for a cycle" as Diff
  usecase "Toggle diff between a\nrendered diagram and the list" as DiffDiagram
  usecase "Read a diagram element's\ndescription" as Desc
  usecase "Accumulate a whole-map\nbaseline across cycles" as WholeMap
}

Dev --> RunCycle
Dev --> Tree
Dev --> Diff
Dev --> Desc
Dev --> WholeMap

Tree ..> Group : <<extend>>
Diff ..> Tree : <<include>>
Diff ..> DiffDiagram : <<extend>>
Tree ..> Desc : <<extend>>
RunCycle ..> WholeMap : <<extend>>

note right of RunCycle
  Code: the /mdd-cycle skill is registered in
  templates::WORKFLOW_SKILLS and shipped as
  SKILL.md to .claude/ and .codex/. Entry
  selection, cycle-boundary ownership, the
  parity loop, and the mandatory clarification
  pause are documented there. The close step
  also rasterizes the cycle diff pumls.
  Realized by SEQ-RUN-CYCLE.
end note

note bottom of Diff
  Code: MddViewer::diff_ui keys on
  self.selected_file. The CYCLE row is built
  from Project::cycles_with_diff_for(file) —
  cycles whose CycleDiff is !is_empty()
  (added/removed; present-unchanged excluded),
  newest first; selected_cycle is constrained
  to that set and defaults to the latest. One
  cycle -> caption; none -> "didn't change in
  any cycle" placeholder. Realized by
  SEQ-RENDER-CYCLE-DIFF.
end note

note bottom of DiffDiagram
  Code: DiffSubMode toggle in diff_ui.
  Diagram resolves Cycle::diff_puml_rel ->
  Project::rendered_svg_path, loads it via
  DiagramPage::load and paints it with the
  shared paint_canvas (pan/zoom reused);
  List renders that one file's element
  buckets. The .diff.svg is pre-rasterized
  by render_cycle_diffs (SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG).
end note

note bottom of Desc
  Code: @desc(<ID>, "text") parsed by
  extract_descs into Project::descriptions();
  shown on selection. Realized by
  SEQ-ELEMENT-DESC.
end note

note bottom of WholeMap
  Code: the "Whole-map baseline" section of
  templates::MDD_CYCLE_SKILL (shipped to
  .claude/ and .codex/ SKILL.md). The Close
  step folds each cycle's CycleDiff into
  .mdd/map/<kind>/<name>.puml (added @ids
  tagged ' @cycle(<ID>,N), removed dropped —
  net, no ghost), rewrites manifest.yml, and
  snapshots .mdd/map/ -> .mdd/cycles/<N>/whole/.
  /mdd-render rasterizes .mdd/map/**.puml.
  Outside the parity gate. Realized by
  SEQ-WHOLE-MAP-ACCUMULATE.
end note
@enduml
